      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; peer review of simulation setup is sufficient.",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup reviewed by a second qualified CFD engineer. Boundary conditions, turbulence model selection, and hemolysis model parameters independently verified. Formal use-error assessment not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis sub-model must be justified for rotating blood pump flows at MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published benchmark comparisons for centrifugal pump flows. Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model is the regulatory standard for CFD hemolysis prediction. Model form adequacy is consistent with MRL 2 expectations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs (fluid properties, rotational speed, inlet flow rate, geometry dimensions) must be documented with sources and nominal values. Uncertainty on inputs must be reported.",
      "rationale": "All 13 model inputs catalogued with nominal values and uncertainty ranges derived from manufacturing tolerances and fluid property literature. Monte Carlo sampling over the full input space was performed with 10,000 draws to propagate input uncertainty to output RH distribution. Input uncertainty ranges are fully characterized; the aggregate output uncertainty is reported as a probability distribution."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
